The Oxford College of Science
A private college established in 1994, located in Bengaluru, India. It is affiliated with Bangalore University and offers undergraduate and postgraduate courses in various science disciplines.  The college is NAAC accredited with an 'A+' grade and approved by AICTE and UGC. It has various campus facilities including a library, laboratories, computer centers, auditorium, hostels, cafeteria, and sports facilities.  The college offers placement and career support services with an average package of approximately â‚¹5 LPA.  It has a student strength of approximately 3,000 and 97 faculty members.  The college has received various rankings and recognitions from publications like India Today and Outlook.
